reviews.text: Happy and casual family run Thai restaurant. Full menu. Great Thai salads and fried rice dishes. Small and popular, so always better to reserve a table.

Some of the best Thai food around! It's a near-ritual at this point to bring newly arrived Thai people here, and they are happy to sing the praises of this place as well. The slightly better plating, more convenient seating and enjoyable views, as well as the opportunity to sit outdoors gives this place the your hand to it's sister restaurant in Sai Kung. Sitting here with some good Thai food and a Singha is very close to the feeling of actually being in Thailand!
Nice food but you have to be very patient as it takes some time for the dishes to arrive

Local Thai restaurant in Saikung and is usually quite busy, but we managed to get a table for two within a few minutes. Food was decent but seemed to be have been modified to local tastes, and the Tom yum goong wasn't spicy at all. That said, I gave it 4 stars because the fried catfish salad "yam plaa doek foo" was really authentic and the best I had in awhile.
Tom Yam Kung was good and staff were friendly.

reviews.text: Lovely staff n food
Very bland Thai food. More staff working than customers but still took 20 mins to deliver flood and same again for anyone to notice it was time to give me my bill.
Service is maintained. Unfortunately food quality is no longer good.  Loss of pure Thai taste.  That might be reason of Michelin recommendation stopped in 2014. Normal price with 10% service charge.
The food there is awesome and satisfactory, will come again for sure.

Regrets. Don't even walk in its not worth your money. Go to the Thai place next to McDonalds or right behind 7/11 by the 1a line. You've been warned. -4 out of 5 I want my money back and my body definitely did not deserve those calories. What a waste of energy. It's just off. Nothing in there tastes like Thai food. 

Here's a quick recap. Curry is watery AF, the duck breast comes from a can, etc. Why is this place in the Michelin Guide Recomendations? No clue. They probably know someone or paid someone a butt load of money because this place don't deserve it.

reviews.text: Lovely staff n food

係貢入西貢影🌟🌟前，搵地方🥢做準備，係泊車方便既萬年街上搵到旺泰，8點零到都坐滿，要坐室外枱，舖頭都好典型泰菜餐廳，掛滿泰皇畫像，樓戊但高，黃燈光，枱少少迫還好，店員識廣東話，不過都有泰式口音🤭

店員推介既生蝦🦐先到，一碟六隻，即係 哈哈哈 蝦蝦蝦😛 每隻都夾左蒜頭🧂同辣椒🌶️係面，點埋佢個清爽微辣汁，將生蝦既爽滑肉質注入動力😯係個口度生蝦咁跳

炸蝦餅🦐都係賣飛弗，四舊水泡樣餅餅上枱，炸得香脆，蝦膠都保持彈性💪另外炸魚餅既香茅味重，同樣用料好，佢係厚身魚餅🐟，同其他泰菜店唔同，好咬啲

至於黃咖哩牛🐂旺泰又係有啲唔同，切左牛肉片，好似中式炒菜咁，不過唔見得特別入味，咖哩汁沾埋蒜蓉包同薄餅都好得💪 again, 佢個薄餅似未發鬆麵包，質感唔同啲，個人建議咖哩都係跟佢蒜蓉包好啲🙄

另外串燒，個熟成啱啱好，無燶邊，肉汁留到係中間🔥 其他舖好多時燒到乾同硬🤭

菠蘿炒飯🍍都好多料，次次呢啲環境都怕做第一個去筆，因為啲料多到好易瀉出黎😜 飯身炒得乾，加埋唔同既海鮮，肉鬆，好充實既口味🤯

兩個炒菜，馬拉戔同咸魚炒都合格有餘😎 唯一要彈少少油

旺泰真係泰菜中既高質，同九龍城既高水準泰菜館係同一檔次😎😎 價錢係西貢黎講算宜人，起碼一定平過食海鮮先🤭

 食完晚飯，直奔北潭涌影🌟🌟
可以一試
